<concept id="en-geometry-window" xml:lang="en-us">
	<title>Geometry window</title>
	<shortdesc>Detailed explanation about how to work with the geometry window.</shortdesc>
	<conbody>
		<p>The Geometry Edit window can be split into 5 sections</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Wing Name</li>
			<li>Leading Edge Section</li>
			<li>Trailing Edge Section</li>
			<li>Vault Section</li>
			<li>Cell distribution section</li>
		</ul>
		<image href="../image/edit-geometry-data-window-en.jpg" alt="Edit Geometry Window" height="365" width="317"/>
		<p>Leading, Trailing Edge and Vault parameters can be edit on the left side of the individual sections.</p>
		<p><b>Leading Edge parameters</b></p>
		<image href="../image/edit-geometry-leading-edge.jpg" alt="Leading Edge parameters" height="291" width="374"/>
		<p><b>Trailing Edge parameters</b></p>
		<image href="../image/edit-geometry-trailing-edge.jpg" alt="Trailing Edge parameters" height="297" width="400"/>
		<p><b>Vault parameters</b></p>
		<p><b>Sin-Cos modif</b></p>
		<image href="../image/edit-geometry-sin-cos.jpg" alt="Sin-Cos Vault parameters" height="356" width="411"/>
		<p><b>Radius-Angle modif</b></p>
		<image href="../image/edit-geometry-ang-rad.jpg" alt="Rad-Ang Vault parameters" height="356" width="411"/>
		<p>Upon pressing <b>[Apply]</b> the individual Graphics on the right will be updated.</p>
		<p>PLEASE NOTE: No parameter checks are implemented currently! There's a chance that the geometry will not be valid.</p>
		<p> </p>
		<p>More explanations can be found on the developer website: <xref href="http://www.laboratoridenvol.com/index.html"> Laboratory d'envol => Software => pre-processor</xref> </p>
	</conbody>
	<related-links>
